\begin{abstract}
  Let $\ell$ be a prime, and $q = p^n$ where $p$ is a prime different
  from $\ell$ and 2.  We show that the $\ell$-completion of the $n$th
  stable homotopy group of spheres is a summand of the
  $\ell$-completion of the $(n,0)$ stable homotopy group of motivic
  spheres over the finite field with $q$ elements ${\mathbb{F}}_q$.  With
  this, and assisted by computer calculations, we are able to compute
  explicitly the two-complete stable motivic stems
  $\pi_{n,0}({\mathbb{F}}_q){{}^{{\kern -.5pt}\wedge}_2}$ for $0\leq n\leq 20$ when $q \equiv 1 \bmod 4$
  and for $0\leq n\leq 18$ when $q \equiv 3 \bmod 4$.
\end{abstract}

